# AXIOM validator seed list — bootstrap addresses for fresh
# wallet installs. Community-maintained: PR against axiom-dist to
# add / retire entries. Wallets fetch this on first launch and
# discover the rest of the network via gossip.
#
# Format: name<TAB>address<TAB>email<TAB>ed25519_pubkey_hex
#
# Address column = validator's SMTP host (currently unused; Kiddo
# opens SMTP, not the wallet).
#
# Ed25519 pubkey (optional, 64 hex chars / 32 bytes — added
# 2026-05-13 per AXIOM_DESIGN_PublicMailCarriers.md §3.1).  When
# present, the SDK derives an X25519 pubkey via to_montgomery()
# and seals UMP bodies to that key (UmpEnvelope::Encrypted);
# absent ⇒ Plain.  Validators with no published pubkey continue
# to work, just unencrypted.
